Pour Chai Tea powder into a small bowl and add boiling water; stir until dissolved. Quick-chill mixture for 10 minutes by nesting bowl in a larger bowl filled with ice water. Stir chai mixture occasionally until cool. Pour cooled tea mixture into a blender. Add milk and orange juice concentrate. Whirl mixture until smoothly blended. Transfer to a large pitcher, then stir in ginger ale to taste. To serve, pour into ice-filled glasses and garnish with orange slices.